Step 1 – Restate the claim and list the arguments  
Claim: *Cayden is a successful restaurateur.*  

Arguments (P-type, all warranted):  

A1 (0.88): Cayden is well traveled → must be either an experienced chef or a successful restaurateur (but not both). Supports possibility of being a restaurateur.  

A2 (0.00): Cayden masters techniques + understands flavors → has culinary skills → could support restaurant success, especially since owning a restaurant requires culinary skills or baking (not both).  

A3 (0.78): Cayden does not enjoy experiments → cannot have a good palate → from “Cayden is either a skilled food critique or has a good palate, but not both” → he may be a skilled food critique rather than a restaurateur (conflicts with claim).  

A4 (0.85): Cayden is culturally aware → from “If culturally aware, then either an experienced chef or a skilled food critique, but not both” → could be an experienced chef, aligning with restaurateur possibility given well-traveled status and culinary skills.  

